Step 1 — Add GitHub Secret
Developers must add a Personal Access Token (PAT) to their repository.
Navigate to:
Repository → Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions
Add a new secret with the following details:
Secret Name
AUTOMATION_PAT
Secret Value
<Personal Access Token provided by the QA team>

Important Notes
The token must have permission to access the Automation Repository
If using Classic PAT, enable the repo scope
If using Fine-grained PAT, ensure:
The automation repository is selected
Required read/write permissions are enabled

Step 2 — Create Workflow Folder
Create the following directory in your repository if it does not already exist:
.github/workflows
This directory stores all GitHub Actions workflow files.

Step 3 — Add Automation Trigger Workflow
Create the following workflow file:
.github/workflows/staging-regression-trigger.yml

name: Regression Gate for Staging
on:
  push:
    branches:
      - staging
  pull_request:
    branches:
      - production
    types:
      - opened
      - reopened
      - synchronize
  workflow_dispatch:
    inputs:
      suite:
        description: Select suite to dispatch to Myndz
        required: true
        default: regression
        type: choice
        options:
          - regression
          - smoke
          - both

concurrency:
  group: regression-gate-${{ github.event_name }}-${{ github.ref }}-${{ github.event.pull_request.number || github.sha }}
  cancel-in-progress: true

jobs:
  regression-gate:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    env:
      TARGET_OWNER: VJqualityanalyst       # Update this to the actual owner of the target repository if different
      TARGET_REPO: XYZ                   # Update this to the actual name of the target repository if different

    steps:
      - name: Trigger Tests in Myndz
        id: trigger
        shell: bash
        run: |
          if [ -z "${{ secrets.AUTOMATION_PAT }}" ]; then
            echo "AUTOMATION_PAT secret is missing in source repo: ${{ github.repository }}"
            echo "Add secret in Cypress repo Settings -> Secrets and variables -> Actions"
            exit 1
          fi

          user_check_status=$(curl -sS -o user_check.json -w "%{http_code}" \
            -H "Accept: application/vnd.github+json" \
            -H "Authorization: Bearer ${{ secrets.AUTOMATION_PAT }}" \
            -H "X-GitHub-Api-Version: 2022-11-28" \
            "https://api.github.com/user")

          echo "Token user check HTTP status: $user_check_status"
          cat user_check.json || true

          if [ "$user_check_status" != "200" ]; then
            echo "Invalid or unusable PAT in AUTOMATION_PAT secret for repo ${{ github.repository }}"
            exit 1
          fi

          repo_check_status=$(curl -sS -o repo_check.json -w "%{http_code}" \
            -H "Accept: application/vnd.github+json" \
            -H "Authorization: Bearer ${{ secrets.AUTOMATION_PAT }}" \
            -H "X-GitHub-Api-Version: 2022-11-28" \
            "https://api.github.com/repos/${TARGET_OWNER}/${TARGET_REPO}")

          echo "Repo access HTTP status: $repo_check_status"
          cat repo_check.json || true

          if [ "$repo_check_status" != "200" ]; then
            echo "Token cannot access ${TARGET_OWNER}/${TARGET_REPO}."
            echo "Important: this workflow reads AUTOMATION_PAT from source repo ${{ github.repository }}, not from ${TARGET_OWNER}/${TARGET_REPO}."
            echo "Use a PAT that has access to the target repo (classic: repo scope; fine-grained: repository selected with required write permissions)."
            exit 1
          fi

          dispatch_event() {
            event_type="$1"
            status_code=$(curl -sS -o response.json -w "%{http_code}" -X POST "https://api.github.com/repos/${TARGET_OWNER}/${TARGET_REPO}/dispatches" \
              -H "Accept: application/vnd.github+json" \
              -H "Authorization: Bearer ${{ secrets.AUTOMATION_PAT }}" \
              -H "X-GitHub-Api-Version: 2022-11-28" \
              -d "{\"event_type\":\"${event_type}\",\"client_payload\":{\"test_folder\":\"automated_tests\",\"source_repo\":\"${{ github.repository }}\",\"source_sha\":\"${{ github.sha }}\",\"source_event\":\"${{ github.event_name }}\",\"source_base_ref\":\"${{ github.base_ref || '' }}\"}}")

            echo "Dispatch '${event_type}' HTTP status: $status_code"
            cat response.json || true

            if [ "$status_code" != "204" ]; then
              echo "Dispatch failed for '${event_type}'. Expected 204 from repository_dispatch API."
              exit 1
            fi
          }

          if [ "${{ github.event_name }}" = "workflow_dispatch" ]; then
            suite="${{ github.event.inputs.suite }}"
          elif [ "${{ github.event_name }}" = "push" ]; then
            suite="regression"
          elif [ "${{ github.event_name }}" = "pull_request" ]; then
            if [ "${{ github.event.action }}" = "synchronize" ] && [ "${{ github.event.pull_request.head.ref }}" = "staging" ]; then
              echo "Skipping smoke on synchronize from staging to avoid duplicate run with push-regression."
              exit 0
            fi
            suite="smoke"
          else
            echo "Unsupported event '${{ github.event_name }}'"
            exit 1
          fi

          if [ "$suite" = "regression" ]; then
            dispatch_event "run-regression"
          elif [ "$suite" = "smoke" ]; then
            dispatch_event "run-smoke"
          elif [ "$suite" = "both" ]; then
            dispatch_event "run-regression"
            dispatch_event "run-smoke"
          else
            echo "Unsupported suite '$suite'"
            exit 1
          fi

          echo "Triggered '$suite' dispatch in ${TARGET_OWNER}/${TARGET_REPO}"

          
How the Workflow Works
Push to Staging
When code is pushed to the staging branch, the workflow will:
Trigger the Regression Test Suite
Validate the staging environment
Pull Request to Production
When a pull request is opened from staging to production, the workflow will:
Trigger the Smoke Test Suite
Validate the production release

Troubleshooting
Issue: Missing AUTOMATION_PAT
Error:
AUTOMATION_PAT secret is missing in source repo
Solution
Add the secret in:
Repository → Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions


